#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossterm><acronym>IO</acronym> Worker</glossterm>"
msgstr "<glossterm><acronym>IO</acronym> कार्यकर्ता</glossterm>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>IO</acronym> Workers enable &kde; applications to access remote "
"resources as easily as local resources (making them \"network transparent"
"\"). Remote resources (&eg; files) might be stored on <acronym>SMB</acronym> "
"shares or similar."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>IO</acronym> श्रमिकाः &kde; अनुप्रयोगाः दूरस्थसंसाधनानाम् अभिगमनाय "
"स्थानीयसंसाधनानाम् इव सुलभतया (तेषां \"जालपारदर्शकं\" कृत्वा) । दूरस्थसंसाधनं (&eg; "
"सञ्चिकाः) <acronym>SMB</acronym> साझेदारी अथवा तत्सदृशेषु संगृहीताः भवेयुः ।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:123
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-smb\"><acronym>SMB</acronym></glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"ग्लोस्-सम्ब\"><acronym>SMB</acronym></glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossseealso\">&kde;</glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "KHTML"
msgstr "KHTML"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"KHTML is the &HTML; rendering engine for the &kde; &plasma; desktop, as used "
"by the &konqueror; browser. It also provides a KPart that enables all &kde; "
"applications to display web content. A new introduction, &Qt; WebKit is also "
"for Plasma and other application development."
msgstr ""
"KHTML इति &HTML; &kde इत्यस्य कृते रेण्डरिंग् इञ्जिनम्; &प्लाज्मा; डेस्कटॉप्, यथा "
"&konqueror; ब्राउज़र। एतत् KPart अपि प्रदाति यत् सर्वाणि &kde; जालसामग्री प्रदर्शयितुं "
"अनुप्रयोगाः। एकः नूतनः परिचयः, &Qt; WebKit प्लाज्मा इत्यादीनां अनुप्रयोगविकासाय अपि "
"अस्ति ।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-konqueror\">&konqueror;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-kparts\">KParts</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm="
"\"gloss-plasma\">&plasma;</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-"
"webkit\">WebKit</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossseealso>&konqueror;</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm="
"\"gloss-kparts\">KParts</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-plasma"
"\">&plasma;</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-webkit\">जालकिट</"
"glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "<acronym>KIO</acronym>"
msgstr "<acronym>KIO</acronym> इति"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &kde; Input/Output system which makes use of so-called \"<acronym>IO</"
"acronym> Workers\"."
msgstr ""
"इति &kde; Input/Output system यत् तथाकथितानां \"<acronym>IO</acronym> Workers"
"\" इत्यस्य उपयोगं करोति ।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-ioworker\"><acronym>IO</acronym> Worker</"
"glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-ioworker\"><acronym>IO</acronym> कार्यकर्ता</"
"glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:148
#, no-c-format
msgid "Kiosk"
msgstr "कियोस्क"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Kiosk is a framework for restricting user capabilities on a &kde; platform "
"system, ideal for use in locked-down environments such as Internet cafés. It "
"is present in &kde; 3 and &kde; 4, but the administration tool, "
"<application>Kiosktool</application> is &kde; 3 only. It can be used to "
"configure &kde; 4 applications, or kiosk configurations can be maintained by "
"editing config files manually."
msgstr ""
"कियोस्कः &kde; मञ्चव्यवस्था, अन्तर्जालकफे इत्यादिषु तालाबन्दी-वातावरणेषु उपयोगाय आदर्शा । "
"इति &kde; ३ तथा &kde; ४, परन्तु प्रशासनसाधनं, <application>Kiosktool</"
"application> &kde; ३ केवलम् । तस्य उपयोगः &kde; ४ अनुप्रयोगाः, अथवा "
"कियोस्कविन्यासाः विन्याससञ्चिकाः मैन्युअल् रूपेण सम्पादयित्वा परिपालयितुं शक्यन्ते ।"

#. Tag: glossseealso
#: index.docbook:150 index.docbook:199 index.docbook:207 index.docbook:287
#: index.docbook:395 index.docbook:531
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso>"
msgstr "<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossseealso\">&यत्र;</glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:154
#, no-c-format
msgid "KParts"
msgstr "केपार्ट्स्"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"KParts is an embedding technology which allows &kde; applications to embed "
"other &kde; applications. For example, the text view used by &konqueror; is "
"a KPart."
msgstr ""
"KParts एकः एम्बेडिंग् प्रौद्योगिकी अस्ति या &kde; अन्येषां &kde; अनुप्रयोगाः। यथा, "
"&konqueror; इति KPart."

#. Tag: glossseealso
#: index.docbook:158 index.docbook:376
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-konqueror\">&konqueror;</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossseealso\">&konqueror;</glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid "KSycoca"
msgstr "केसाइकोका"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:163
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<acronym>KSycoca</acronym> (&kde; &emstart;Sy&emend;stem &emstart;Co&emend;"
"nfiguration &emstart;Ca&emend;che) is a configuration cache which, for "
"example, guarantees fast access to the menu entries."
msgstr ""
"<acronym>KSycoca</acronym> (&kde; &emstart;Sy&emend;stem &emstart;Co&emend;"
"nfiguration &emstart;Ca&emend;che) एकः विन्याससञ्चयः अस्ति यः, उदाहरणार्थं, "
"मेनूप्रविष्टीनां द्रुतप्रवेशस्य गारण्टीं ददाति"

#. Tag: application
#: index.docbook:168 index.docbook:261
#, no-c-format
msgid "KBuildSycoca"
msgstr "केबिल्डसाइकोका"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "Platform"
msgstr "तमङ्गः"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Previously the base of libraries and services needed to run &kde; "
"applications. It is used by core and third-party developers to create &kde; "
"software. Especially when including development frameworks and tools it may "
"be referred to as &kde; Development Platform. &kde; Platform is built on a "
"number of Pillars, for example Akonadi, Solid, Phonon."
msgstr ""
"पूर्वं पुस्तकालयानाम् सेवानां च आधारः चालयितुं आवश्यकः आसीत् &kde; अनुप्रयोगाः। अस्य उपयोगः "
"कोर-तृतीय-पक्ष-विकासकैः &kde; तन्त्रांश। विशेषतः यदा विकासरूपरेखाः साधनानि च "
"समाविष्टानि सन्ति तदा तत् &kde; विकास मञ्च। &kde; मञ्चः अनेकेषु स्तम्भेषु निर्मितः अस्ति, "
"यथा अकोनाडी, सॉलिड्, फोनोन् ।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-plasma\">&plasma;</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm="
"\"gloss-applications\">Applications</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm="
"\"gloss-frameworks\">Frameworks</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm="
"\"gloss-akonadi\">Akonadi</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-"
"solid\">Solid</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-phonon"
"\">Phonon</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-plasma\">&plasma;</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm="
"\"gloss-applications\">अनुप्रयोग</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm="
"\"gloss-frameworks\">रूपरेखा</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-"
"akonadi\">अकोनाडी</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-solid"
"\">ठोस</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"glosss- phonon\">फोनो</"
"glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:185
#, no-c-format
msgid "Phonon"
msgstr "फोनोन्"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:186
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A cross-platform multimedia API, interfacing with existing frameworks, such "
"as gstreamer and xine engines. &kde; 2 and 3 depended on aRts for sound. "
"Phonon replaces it.&newpara; More info:&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://en."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/Phonon_(software)\"&linkmid; Wikipedia: Phonon "
"(software)&linkend;&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://phonon.kde.org/\"&linkmid;"
"Phonon website&linkend;"
msgstr ""
"एकः क्रॉस्-प्लेटफॉर्म मल्टीमीडिया एपिआइ, विद्यमानरूपरेखाभिः सह अन्तरफलकं, यथा gstreamer "
"तथा xine इञ्जिन् । &kde; २ तथा ३ शब्दस्य कृते aRts आश्रिताः आसन् । तस्य स्थाने फोनोनः "
"भवति।&newpara; अधिकविवरणम्:&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://hi.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/Phonon_(सॉफ्टवेयर)\"&linkmid; विकिपीडिया: फोनोन (सॉफ्टवेयर)&linkend;"
"&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://phonon.kde.org/\"&linkmid;फोनन वेबसाइट&linkend;"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:189
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-arts\">aRts</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-arts\">कला</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:195
#, no-c-format
msgid "Solid"
msgstr "ठोस"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:196
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Solid provides a single API for hardware management. Hardware is grouped "
"into 'domains'. Since the backends for Solid are pluggable, Solid helps "
"application developers write less code, and have it platform independent."
"&newpara; More info:&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://solid.kde.org/\"&linkmid;"
"Discover Solid&linkend;"
msgstr ""
"Solid इत्यनेन हार्डवेयरप्रबन्धनार्थं एकं API प्रदाति । हार्डवेयर 'डोमेन्स्' इत्यत्र समूहीकृतः "
"अस्ति । यतः Solid कृते पृष्ठभागाः प्लग्योग्याः सन्ति, Solid अनुप्रयोगविकासकानाम् न्यूनसङ्केतं "
"लिखितुं साहाय्यं करोति, तथा च तस्य मञ्चस्वतन्त्रं भवति।&newpara; अधिकविवरणम्:&newpara; "
"&linkstart;\"https://solid.kde.org/\"&linkmid;ठोसस्य अन्वेषणं&linkend;"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:203
#, no-c-format
msgid "Threadweaver"
msgstr "सूत्रधारी"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:204
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This thread programming library spreads work among multiple-core processors "
"where available, prioritizing them before queuing them for execution. "
"ThreadWeaver provides a high-level job interface for multithreaded "
"programming.&newpara; More info:&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://api.kde.org/"
"frameworks/threadweaver/html/index.html\"&linkmid;API Documentation – "
"ThreadWeaver&linkend;"
msgstr ""
"इदं थ्रेड् प्रोग्रामिंग लाइब्रेरी यत्र उपलब्धं तत्र बहु-कोर-प्रोसेसर-मध्ये कार्यं प्रसारयति, "
"निष्पादनार्थं पङ्क्तिं कर्तुं पूर्वं तान् प्राथमिकताम् अददात् । ThreadWeaver बहुथ्रेडेड् "
"प्रोग्रामिंग् कृते उच्चस्तरीयं कार्य-अन्तरफलकं प्रदाति।&newpara; अधिकविवरणम्:&newpara; "
"&linkstart;\"https://api.kde.org/frameworks/threadweaver/html/index.html"
"\"&linkmid;एपीआई दस्तावेजीकरणम् – थ्रेडवीवर&linkend;"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:211
#, no-c-format
msgid "WebKit"
msgstr "WebKit"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:212
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"HTML rendering engine, originating from a fork of KHTML. Adopted by "
"<trademark>Apple</trademark> and developed for <trademark>Safari</"
"trademark>. Webkit brings the whole functionality back to &kde; SC 4, where "
"it is available through &Qt;.&newpara; More info:&newpara; &linkstart;"
"\"https://webkit.org/\"&linkmid;WebKit home page&linkend;&newpara; "
"&linkstart;\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WebKit\"&linkmid;Wikipedia: "
"WebKit&linkend;"
msgstr ""
"HTML रेण्डरिंग् इञ्जिन्, KHTML इत्यस्य एकस्मात् हंसात् उत्पन्नम् । <trademark>Apple</"
"trademark> द्वारा स्वीकृतं <trademark>Safari</trademark> कृते च विकसितम् । Webkit "
"सम्पूर्णं कार्यक्षमतां पुनः &kde; SC 4, यत्र &Qt;.&newpara; अधिकविवरणम्:&newpara; "
"&linkstart;\"https://webkit.org/\"&linkmid;वेबकिटस्य मुखपृष्ठं&linkend;&newpara; "
"&linkstart;\"https://hi.wikipedia.org/wiki/WebKit\"&linkmid;विकिपीडिया: "
"वेबकिट&linkend;"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:215
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-khtml\">KHTML</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-khtml\">KHTML</glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:223
#, no-c-format
msgid "X.Org"
msgstr "X.Org"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:225
#, no-c-format
msgid "Antialiasing"
msgstr "Antialiasing इति"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:226
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If mentioned in context with &kde;, anti-aliasing often means the smoothing "
"of the fonts visible on the screen. &Qt; version 3.3 or higher used together "
"with X.Org server makes this possible under &kde; as well."
msgstr ""
"यदि &kde; इत्यनेन सह सन्दर्भे उल्लिखितं तर्हि एण्टी-एलियासिंग् इत्यस्य अर्थः प्रायः पर्दायां "
"दृश्यमानानां फ़ॉन्ट्-इत्यस्य स्निग्धीकरणं भवति । &Qt; X.Org सर्वरेण सह एकत्र उपयुज्यमानं "
"संस्करणं 3.3 अथवा उच्चतरं &kde; अपि।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-qt\">&Qt;</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterms=\"gloss-chain\">&शृङ्खला;</glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterms=\"gloss-qt\">&Qt;</glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:235
#, no-c-format
msgid "&X-Server;"
msgstr "&X-सर्वर;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:236
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &X-Server; represents a basic layer upon which the various &GUI;s like "
"&kde; are built. It manages the basic mouse and keyboard input (from the "
"local host as well as from remote hosts) and provides elementary graphic "
"routines to draw rectangles and other primitives."
msgstr ""
"&X-सर्वरः; एकं मूलभूतं स्तरं प्रतिनिधियति यस्मिन् &kde; निर्मिताः भवन्ति। इदं मूलभूतं माउस-"
"कीबोर्ड-निवेशं (स्थानीय-होस्ट्-तः अपि च दूरस्थ-होस्ट्-तः) प्रबन्धयति तथा च आयत-आदि-आदि-"
"आदि-आकर्षणार्थं प्राथमिक-ग्राफिक-रूटीन-प्रदानं करोति"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-gui\">&GUI;</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-gui\">&GUI;</glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:248
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Applications</title>"
msgstr "<title>अनुप्रयोगाः</title>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:250
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dolphin"
msgstr "डॉल्फिन"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:251
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default file manager in &kde; Applications. It has a side panel "
"(Places), but navigation is mainly by the 'breadcrumb' trail above the main "
"window. Split windows are possible, and views can be applied to individual "
"windows. Mounting and unmounting <acronym>USB</acronym> devices can be done "
"in the side panel. Other directories can be added to the Places panel. A "
"Tree view is also possible.&newpara; More info:&newpara; &linkstart;"
"\"https://www.kde.org/applications/system/dolphin/\"&linkmid;Dolphin&linkend;"
"&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Dolphin_(file_manager)\"&linkmid;Wikipedia: Dolphin&linkend;&newpara; "
"&linkstart;\"https://userbase.kde.org/Dolphin/File_Management\"&linkmid;"
"Userbase: File Management Tutorial&linkend;"
msgstr ""
"&kde;मध्ये पूर्वनिर्धारितः सञ्चिकाप्रबन्धकः; अनुप्रयोगाः। अस्य पार्श्वपटलः (Places) अस्ति, "
"परन्तु मुख्यजालकस्य उपरि 'ब्रेड्क्रम्ब'-पन्थेन मुख्यतया मार्गदर्शनं भवति । विभक्तविण्डोः "
"सम्भवन्ति, व्यक्तिगतविण्डोषु च दृश्यानि प्रयोक्तुं शक्यन्ते । <acronym>USB</acronym> "
"उपकरणानां माउण्टिङ्ग्, अनमाउण्टिङ्ग् च पार्श्वफलके कर्तुं शक्यते । अन्यनिर्देशिकाः Places "
"फलकस्य मध्ये योजयितुं शक्यन्ते । वृक्षदृश्यमपि सम्भवति।&newpara; अधिकविवरणम्:&newpara; "
"&linkstart;\"https://www.kde.org/applications/system/dolphin/\"&linkmid;"
"डॉल्फिन&linkend;&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://hi.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Dolphin_(file_manager)\"&linkmid;विकिपीडिया: डॉल्फिन&linkend;&newpara; "
"&linkstart;\"https://userbase.kde.org/Dolphin/File_Management\"&linkmid;"
"उपयोक्तृकोषः: सञ्चिकाप्रबन्धनपाठ्यक्रम&linkend;"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:255
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-konqueror\">&konqueror;</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossseealso\">&konqueror;</glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:262
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<application>KBuildSycoca4</application> is a command line program and "
"regenerates the so-called <acronym>KSycoca</acronym>. This is useful, for "
"example, if some or all modules in &systemsettings; are missing."
msgstr ""
"<application>KBuildSycoca4</application> एकः आदेशपङ्क्तिकार्यक्रमः अस्ति तथा च "
"तथाकथितं <acronym>KSycoca</acronym> पुनः जनयति । एतत् उपयोगी भवति, उदाहरणार्थं, "
"यदि &systemsettings; लुप्ताः सन्ति।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:266
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-ksycoca\"><acronym>KSycoca</acronym></"
"glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-systemsettings"
"\">&systemsettings;</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-ksycoca\"><acronym>KSycoca</acronym></"
"glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-systemsettings\">&प्रणालीसेटिंग्स्;"
"</glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:272
#, no-c-format
msgid "KInfoCenter"
msgstr "किन्फोसेन्टर"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:273
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Kinfocenter originated as part of Kcontrol standing alone from KDE 3.1. In "
"&kde; SC 4 it was replaced by modules configured in &systemsettings;, "
"notably Solid, and is being reintroduced as an application in &plasma;."
"&newpara; More info:&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://www.kde.org/applications/"
"system/kinfocenter/\"&linkmid;KInfoCenter&linkend;&newpara; &linkstart;"
"\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kinfocenter\"&linkmid;Wikipedia: "
"KInfoCenter&linkend;"
msgstr ""
"Kinfocenter इत्यस्य उत्पत्तिः KDE 3.1 इत्यस्मात् एकान्ते स्थितस्य Kcontrol इत्यस्य भागरूपेण "
"अभवत् । इत्यत्र &kde; SC 4 तस्य स्थाने &systemsettings;, विशेषतः Solid इत्यत्र "
"विन्यस्तैः मॉड्यूलैः स्थापितं, &plasma;.&newpara; अधिकविवरणम्:&newpara; &linkstart;"
"\"https://www.kde.org/अनुप्रयोग/प्रणाली/किन्फोसेन्टर/\"&linkmid;"
"KInfoCenter&linkend;&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://hi.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Kinfocenter\"&linkmid;विकिपीडिया: KInfoCenter&linkend;"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:276
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-solid\">Solid</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm="
"\"gloss-systemsettings\">&systemsettings;</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-solid\">ठोस</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-"
"systemsettings\">&systemsettings;</glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:283
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossterm>&konqueror;</glossterm>"
msgstr "<glossterm>&konqueror;</glossterm> इति"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:284
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&konqueror; is a web browser, picture viewer, file manager and more, and a "
"core part of the &kde; project. You can find more information about "
"&konqueror; at &linkstart;\"https://konqueror.org/\"&linkmid;www.konqueror."
"org&linkend;."
msgstr ""
"&konqueror; एकः जालपुटः, चित्रदर्शकः, सञ्चिकाप्रबन्धकः इत्यादयः, &kde; प्रकल्प। "
"&konqueror; at &linkstart;\"https://konqueror.org/\"&linkmid;www.konqueror."
"org&linkend;."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:291
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossterm>KRunner</glossterm>"
msgstr "<glossterm>KRunner</glossterm> इति"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:292
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The mini-command-line that is accessed from the Classic menu, the keyboard "
"shortcut &Alt;+<keycap>F2</keycap>, or a right-click on the desktop. In "
"&kde; SC 4 a partial name will display all possible matches.&newpara; More "
"info:&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://userbase.kde.org/Plasma/Krunner"
"\"&linkmid;UserBase: KRunner Usage&linkend;"
msgstr ""
"Classic मेन्यूतः, कीबोर्ड-शॉर्टकट् &Alt;+<keycap>F2</keycap>तः, अथवा डेस्कटॉप्-उपरि "
"दक्षिण-क्लिक् कृत्वा या लघु-आदेश-पङ्क्तिः अभिगता भवति । इत्यत्र &kde; SC 4 एकं आंशिकं नाम "
"सर्वाणि सम्भाव्यमेलनानि प्रदर्शयिष्यति।&newpara; अधिकविवरणम्:&newpara; &linkstart;"
"\"https://userbase.kde.org/Plasma/Krunner\"&linkmid;उपयोक्तृबेस: KRunner "
"उपयोगः&linkend;"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:300
#, no-c-format
msgid "KWin"
msgstr "केविन्"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:301
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"KWin is the window manager. This is where window decorations can be changed "
"and themes applied. &kde; SC 4 extends KWin to provide support for 3D "
"Compositing effects on the desktop.&newpara; More info:&newpara; &linkstart;"
"\"https://userbase.kde.org/KWin\"&linkmid;UserBase: KWin&linkend;"
msgstr ""
"KWin इति विण्डो प्रबन्धकः । अत्रैव खिडकी-सज्जाः परिवर्तयितुं विषयाः च प्रयोक्तुं शक्यन्ते । "
"&kde; SC 4 डेस्कटॉप् मध्ये 3D Compositing प्रभावानां समर्थनं प्रदातुं KWin इत्यस्य विस्तारं "
"करोति।&newpara; अधिकविवरणम्:&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://userbase.kde.org/"
"KWin\"&linkmid;उपयोक्तृआधारः KWin&linkend;"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-xserver\">&X-Server;</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-xserver\">&X-सर्वर;</glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:309
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mini-CLI"
msgstr "लघु-सीएलआई"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:310
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Mini &emstart;C&emend;ommand &emstart;L&emend;ine &emstart;I&emend;nterface. "
"Synonym to KRunner."
msgstr ""
"मिनी &emstart;C&emend;command &emstart;L&emend;ine &emstart;I&emend;"
"interface. KRunner का पर्यायवाची।"

#. Tag: glossseealso
#: index.docbook:311
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-krunner\">KRunner</glossseealso>"
msgstr "<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-krunner\">क्रनर</glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:315
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pager"
msgstr "पेजर"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:316
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A pager is a small program or panel applet which shows the position of "
"windows on your desktop and usually if you have several Virtual Desktops "
"gives an overview over all."
msgstr ""
"पेजरः एकः लघुः प्रोग्राम् अथवा पैनल एप्लेट् अस्ति यः भवतः डेस्कटॉप् मध्ये विण्डोस् स्थानं "
"दर्शयति तथा च सामान्यतया यदि भवतः समीपे अनेकाः वर्चुअल् डेस्कटॉप् सन्ति तर्हि सर्वेषु "
"अवलोकनं ददाति ।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:316
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-application-starter\">Application Starter</glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kicker\">Kicker</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-panel\">Panel</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm="
"\"gloss-plasma\">&plasma;</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-"
"virtualdesktops\">Virtual Desktops</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-application-starter\">अनुप्रयोग प्रारम्भ</glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kicker\">किकर</glossseealso> < glossseealso "
"इति otherterm=\"gloss-panel\">पैनल</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm="
"\"gloss-plasma\">&plasma;</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-"
"virtualdesktops\">आभासी डेस्कटॉप</glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:326
#, no-c-format
msgid "&systemsettings;"
msgstr "&प्रणालीसेटिंग्स्;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:327
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the project and filename of the &kde; control center. "
"&systemsettings; allows you to customize virtually every configuration "
"option of &kde;."
msgstr ""
"एतत् &kde; नियन्त्रण केन्द्र। &प्रणालीसेटिंग्स्; &kde; इत्यस्य प्रायः प्रत्येकं विन्यासविकल्पं "
"अनुकूलितुं शक्नोति ।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:329
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-kinfocenter\">KInfoCenter</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-kinfocenter\">किंफोकेन्द्र</glossseealso>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:337
#, no-c-format
msgid "Desktop Terminology"
msgstr "डेस्कटॉप शब्दावली"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid "Activities"
msgstr "गतिविधयः"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Activities are sets of &plasma; widgets that have their own "
"wallpaper&newpara; A bit like Virtual Desktops, but not quite. For example "
"you have a \"work activity\" with commit rss feeds, a note with your TODO, a "
"Folder View with your work related files, and a subtle wallpaper.&newpara; "
"Next to it, you have your freetime activity, with previews of family photos "
"and dogs, rss feeds from your favorite blogs, a Folder View showing your "
"movie collection, a twitter applet and of course that Iron Maiden wallpaper "
"you have been loving since the early 80s.&newpara; At 17:00 hours sharp you "
"switch from the work activity to your freetime activity.&newpara; More info:"
"&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://userbase.kde.org/Plasma\"&linkmid;Plasma "
"FAQ&linkend;"
msgstr ""
"क्रियाकलापाः &plasma; विजेट् येषां स्वकीयः वॉलपेपरः&newpara; किञ्चित् Virtual "
"Desktops इव, परन्तु सर्वथा न। उदाहरणार्थं भवतः commit rss फीड्स् इत्यनेन सह "
"\"कार्यक्रियाकलापः\", भवतः TODO इत्यनेन सह टिप्पणी, भवतः कार्यसम्बद्धसञ्चिकाभिः सह "
"Folder View, सूक्ष्मः वॉलपेपरः च अस्ति ।&newpara तस्य पार्श्वे भवतः अवकाशसमयस्य "
"क्रियाकलापः अस्ति, यत्र परिवारस्य छायाचित्रस्य श्वानानां च पूर्वावलोकनं, भवतः प्रियब्लॉग्-"
"तः rss-फीड्, भवतः चलच्चित्रसङ्ग्रहं दर्शयति Folder View, twitter applet तथा च "
"निश्चितरूपेण सः Iron Maiden wallpaper यः भवतः प्रारम्भात् एव प्रेम्णा भवति 80s."
"&newpara; १७:०० वादने तीक्ष्णसमये भवान् कार्यक्रियाकलापात् स्वस्य विरक्तसमयक्रियाकलापं "
"प्रति स्विच करोति।&newpara; अधिकविवरणम्:&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://userbase."
"kde.org/प्लाज्मा\"&linkmid;प्लाज्मा FAQ&linkend;"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:345
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-virtualdesktops\">Virtual Desktops</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-virtualdesktops\">आभासी डेस्कटॉप</glossseealso>"

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:351
#, no-c-format
msgid "Breeze"
msgstr "वायुः"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:352
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Breeze is the default theme for &plasma;. The new theme is a high-contrast, "
"flat theme for the workspace. It is available in light and dark variants. "
"Simpler and more monochromatic graphics assets and typography-centered "
"layouts offer a clean and visually clear user experience."
msgstr ""
"Breeze &plasma; इत्यस्य पूर्वनिर्धारितः विषयः अस्ति । नूतनः विषयः कार्यक्षेत्रस्य कृते उच्च-"
"विपरीतः, सपाटः विषयः अस्ति । इदं प्रकाश-अन्धकार-रूपेषु उपलभ्यते । सरलतराणि अधिकानि च "
"एकवर्णीयाः ग्राफिक्स्-सम्पत्तयः मुद्रण-केन्द्रित-विन्यासाः च स्वच्छं दृग्गत-स्पष्टं च उपयोक्तृ-"
"अनुभवं प्रददति ।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:352
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-ksvg\">KSVG</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-"
"plasma\">&plasma;</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-oxygen"
"\">Oxygen</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-ksvg\">KSVG</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-"
"plasma\">&प्लाज्मा;</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-oxygen"
"\">आक्सीजन</glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:360
#, no-c-format
msgid "Containment"
msgstr "निरोधः"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:361
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A Containment is a top level grouping of widgets. Each Containment manages "
"the layout and configuration data of its set of widgets independently from "
"other Containments.&newpara; The end result is that you can group widgets "
"within a Containment according to the significance to your working pattern, "
"rather than by directory grouping.&newpara; More info:&newpara; &linkstart;"
"\"https://userbase.kde.org/Plasma\"&linkmid;Plasma FAQ&linkend;"
msgstr ""
"Containment इति विजेट्-समूहस्य शीर्षस्तरीयः समूहीकरणं भवति । प्रत्येकं Containment "
"अन्येभ्यः Containments इत्यस्मात् स्वतन्त्रतया स्वस्य विजेट्-समूहस्य विन्यास-विन्यास-दत्तांशं "
"प्रबन्धयति ।&newpara; अन्त्यफलं यत् भवान् निर्देशिकासमूहीकरणेन न अपितु स्वस्य "
"कार्यप्रतिमानस्य महत्त्वस्य अनुसारं Containment इत्यस्य अन्तः विजेट् समूहयितुं शक्नोति।"
"&newpara; अधिकविवरणम्:&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://userbase.kde.org/प्लाज्मा"
"\"&linkmid;प्लाज्मा FAQ&linkend;"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:364
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-widget\">Widget</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-widget\">विजेट्</glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:370
#, no-c-format
msgid "Drag and Drop"
msgstr "Drag and Drop इति"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This concept tries to replace many actions like copying files from one place "
"to another by a certain mouse movement, &eg; clicking on an icon in a "
"&konqueror; window, moving the mouse to another window while keeping the "
"mouse button pressed, and releasing the mouse button (\"dropping\" the "
"object) copies files."
msgstr ""
"एषा अवधारणा एकस्मात् स्थानात् अन्यस्मिन् स्थाने सञ्चिकानां प्रतिलिपिः इत्यादीनां बहूनां "
"क्रियाणां स्थाने कस्यचित् मूषकस्य गतिं स्थापयितुं प्रयतते, &eg; &konqueror; विण्डो, मूषकस्य "
"बटनं दबावन् अन्यस्मिन् विण्डो मध्ये स्थानान्तरणं कृत्वा, मूषकस्य बटनं मुक्तं कृत्वा (वस्तुं \"पातयन्"
"\") सञ्चिकानां प्रतिलिपिं करोति ।"

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:380
#, no-c-format
msgid "GNOME"
msgstr "GNOME इति"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:382
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&emstart;G&emend;NU &emstart;N&emend;etwork &emstart;O&emend;bject &emstart;"
"M&emend;odel &emstart;E&emend;nvironment, one of the leading &UNIX; &GUI;s."
msgstr ""
"&emstart;G&emend;NU &emstart;N&emend;etwork &emstart;O&emend;bject &emstart;"
"M&emend;odel &emstart;E&emend;nvironment, प्रमुखेषु &UNIX; &GUI;s."

#. Tag: glossseealso
#: index.docbook:385 index.docbook:415
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-gui\">&GUI;</glossseealso>"
msgstr "<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-gui\">&GUI;</glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:389
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossterm>&GUI;</glossterm>"
msgstr "<glossterm>&GUI;</glossterm> इति"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:390
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Abbreviation for &emstart;G&emend;raphical &emstart;U&emend;ser &emstart;"
"I&emend;nterface. Every desktop environment (like &kde;) is a &GUI;. Most "
"&GUI;s feature mouse support and/or windows to manage the programs."
msgstr ""
"&emstart;G&emend;raphical &emstart;U&emend;ser &emstart;I&emend;interface "
"इत्यस्य संक्षिप्तीकरणं। प्रत्येकं डेस्कटॉप् वातावरणं (&kde; इव) &GUI; अधिकांशः &GUI;s "
"कार्यक्रमानां प्रबन्धनार्थं मूषकसमर्थनं तथा/वा विण्डोस् दर्शयति ।"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:399
#, no-c-format
msgid "Home Directory"
msgstr "गृहनिर्देशिका"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:400
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"That's the place in system, where all your files are kept. You can write "
"your files outside of this folder, but all applications are configured to "
"propose this folder as place to write your files to. And this is easier, "
"when you are keeping your things here.&newpara; More info:&newpara; "
"&linkstart;\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Home_directory\"&linkmid;"
"Wikipedia: Home Directory&linkend;"
msgstr ""
"तत् स्थानं सिस्टम् मध्ये, यत्र भवतः सर्वाणि सञ्चिकाः स्थापितानि सन्ति । भवान् अस्य पुटस्य "
"बहिः स्वसञ्चिकाः लिखितुं शक्नोति, परन्तु सर्वे अनुप्रयोगाः विन्यस्ताः यत् एतत् पुटं भवतः "
"सञ्चिकाः लिखितुं स्थानरूपेण प्रस्तावितुं शक्नुवन्ति । एतत् च सुकरं भवति, यदा भवन्तः अत्र "
"स्ववस्तूनि स्थापयन्ति।&newpara; अधिकविवरणम्:&newpara; &linkstart;\"https://hi."
"wikipedia.org/wiki/Home_directory\"&linkmid;विकिपीडिया: गृहनिर्देशिका&linkend;"

#. Tag: glossseealso
#: index.docbook:403
#, no-c-format
msgid "&dolphin;"
msgstr "&डॉल्फिन;"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: index.docbook:407
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossterm>&kde;</glossterm>"
msgstr "<glossterm>&where;</glossterm> इति"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:408
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kde; is more than just software. It is a community made up of programmers, "
"translators, contributors, artists, writers, distributors, and users from "
"all over the world. Our international technology team is committed to "
"creating the best free software for the desktop. And not only contributors, "
"but users and fans of &kde; software can be found throughout the entire "
"globe, giving help to other users, spreading the news, or just simply "
"enjoying the experience. You can find more detailed information at "
"&linkstart;\"https://www.kde.org\"&linkmid;www.kde.org&linkend;.&newpara; "
"The name changed its meaning over time. You can discover more about its "
"history over &linkstart;\"https://www.kde.org/community/history/\"&linkmid;"
"the KDE history webpage&linkend;."
msgstr ""
"&kde; केवलं सॉफ्टवेयर इत्यस्मात् अधिकम् अस्ति। इदं विश्वस्य सर्वेभ्यः प्रोग्रामर-अनुवादक-"
"योगदातृभिः, कलाकारैः, लेखकैः, वितरकैः, उपयोक्तृभिः च निर्मितः समुदायः अस्ति । अस्माकं "
"अन्तर्राष्ट्रीयप्रौद्योगिकीदलः डेस्कटॉपस्य कृते उत्तमं मुक्तसॉफ्टवेयरं निर्मातुं प्रतिबद्धः अस्ति। "
"तथा च न केवलं योगदातारः, अपितु &kde; सॉफ्टवेयर सम्पूर्णे विश्वे द्रष्टुं शक्यते, अन्येभ्यः "
"उपयोक्तृभ्यः साहाय्यं दत्त्वा, वार्ता प्रसारयितुं, अथवा केवलं अनुभवस्य आनन्दं लभते । "
"अधिकविस्तृतसूचनाः &linkstart;\"https://www.kde.org\"&linkmid;www.kde."
"org&linkend;&newpara; कालान्तरे अस्य नामस्य अर्थः परिवर्तितः । भवान् तस्य इतिहासस्य "
"विषये अधिकं &linkstart;\"https://www.kde.org/community/history/\"&linkmid;KDE "
"इतिहासजालपुट&linkend; इत्यस्य माध्यमेन आविष्कर्तुं शक्नोति ।"

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:419
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kicker;"
msgstr "&किकर;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:421
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &kde; 3, the relocatable bar, usually at the bottom of the screen "
"(sometimes called the Panel), on which application launchers, the Pager, and "
"buttons for running applications reside."
msgstr ""
"इत्यत्र &kde; ३, स्थानान्तरणीयपट्टिका, प्रायः स्क्रीनस्य अधः (कदाचित् Panel इति उच्यते), "
"यस्मिन् अनुप्रयोगप्रक्षेपकाः, पेजरः, अनुप्रयोगानाम् चालनार्थं बटन् च निवसन्ति"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:421
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-panel\">Panel</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-plasma\">&plasma;</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-panel\">पैनल</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-plasma\">&प्लाज्मा;</glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:427
#, no-c-format
msgid "Application Starter"
msgstr "अनुप्रयोग प्रारम्भक"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:429
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &plasma; an application launcher in which apps are sorted by functional "
"group. 'Favorites' replaces the 'Most used applications' in Classic Menu, "
"and applications can be added to it. Right-click also offers the possibility "
"of adding applications to the desktop or panel. Rapid access to a less-used "
"application can be by the search box. Alternatives like the classic "
"Application Menu with cascading popup menus and the Application Dashboard, a "
"fullscreen launcher are available. &plasma; can be used with more than one "
"launcher, should that be required.&newpara;"
msgstr ""
"इत्यत्र &प्लाज्मा; एकः अनुप्रयोगप्रक्षेपकः यस्मिन् एप्स् कार्यात्मकसमूहेन क्रमबद्धाः भवन्ति । "
"'Favorites' इत्येतत् Classic Menu इत्यस्मिन् 'Most used applications' इत्यस्य स्थाने "
"भवति, तस्मिन् च अनुप्रयोगाः योजयितुं शक्यन्ते । राइट्-क्लिक् इत्यनेन डेस्कटॉप् अथवा पैनल् इत्यत्र "
"अनुप्रयोगाः योजयितुं सम्भावना अपि प्राप्यते । अल्पप्रयुक्तस्य अनुप्रयोगस्य द्रुतप्रवेशः "
"अन्वेषणपेटिकाद्वारा भवितुम् अर्हति । कैस्केडिंग् पॉपअप मेन्यू सहितं क्लासिक एप्लिकेशन मेनु "
"इत्यादयः विकल्पाः तथा च एप्लिकेशन डैशबोर्ड्, पूर्णपर्दे लॉन्चर इत्यादयः विकल्पाः उपलभ्यन्ते । "
"&प्लाज्मा; एकादशाधिकप्रक्षेपकैः सह उपयोक्तुं शक्यते, यदि तत् आवश्यकं भवेत्।&newpara;"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:430
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-pager\">Pager</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm="
"\"gloss-panel\">Panel</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-plasma"
"\">&plasma;</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-pager\">पेजर</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-"
"panel\">पैनल</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-plasma\">&प्लाज्मा;"
"</glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: acronym
#: index.docbook:438
#, no-c-format
msgid "Oxygen"
msgstr "आक्सीजन"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:440
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Oxygen was the default theme of &kde; SC 4. Designed to bring 'a breath of "
"fresh air' to the desktop by removing the simplistic, cartoonish icons, and "
"replacing them with a clean theme and photo-realistic icons. Oxygen uses a "
"desaturated palette to avoid the icons becoming a distraction and uses "
"detailed scalable graphics (SVG).&newpara; More info:&newpara; &linkstart;"
"\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oxygen_Project\"&linkmid;Wikipedia: Oxygen "
"Project&linkend;"
msgstr ""
"आक्सीजनः &kde; SC 4. सरलं, कार्टुनिश् चिह्नं हृत्वा, तेषां स्थाने स्वच्छविषयं, फोटो-"
"वास्तविकचिह्नानि च स्थापयित्वा डेस्कटॉप् मध्ये 'ताजवायुः' आनेतुं डिजाइनं कृतम्। आक्सीजनः "
"चिह्नानां विक्षेपं न भवितुं विसंतृप्तपैलेट् इत्यस्य उपयोगं करोति तथा च विस्तृतं स्केल-करणीय-"
"ग्राफिक्स् (SVG) इत्यस्य उपयोगं करोति ।&newpara; अधिकविवरणम्:&newpara; &linkstart;"
"\"https://hi.wikipedia.org/wiki/आक्सीजन_परियोजना\"&linkmid;विकिपीडिया: आक्सीजन "
"परियोजना&linkend;"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: index.docbook:442
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-ksvg\">KSVG</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-"
"plasma\">&plasma;</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-breeze"
"\">Breeze</glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-kde\">&kde;</glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"gloss-ksvg\">KSVG</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-"
"plasma\">&प्लाज्मा;</glossseealso> <glossseealso otherterm=\"gloss-breeze"
"\">वायु</glossseealso> इति"

